# r-shiny-filter

## Functionality
A standalone R Shiny web application for interactive environmental data filtering and analysis. Provides a browser-based UI for loading, filtering, and exploring environmental measurement datasets with reactive data tables and visualizations.

## Tasks
- Load environmental data from CSV files (`sample_data.csv` or user uploads)
- Provide interactive data filtering controls (by parameter, date range, location, etc.)
- Display filtered results in reactive data tables
- Generate summary statistics and visualizations for filtered subsets
- Export filtered data

## Purpose
Serves as a **standalone companion tool** to the main Tauri desktop app. While the desktop app handles compliance assessment, this R Shiny module provides advanced, R-native data exploration and filtering for environmental scientists who prefer browser-based workflows. Also useful when the desktop app is not installed.

## General Roadmap
- Currently `r-shiny-filter/app.R` (~27KB) — a self-contained Shiny app
- `install_packages.R` handles dependency installation
- `sample_data.csv` provides demo data
- Future: integrate as a tab within the main Tauri app via embedded webview
- Future: bidirectional data sync with the main app

## Key Files
- `r-shiny-filter/app.R` — Main Shiny application
- `r-shiny-filter/install_packages.R` — R package installer
- `r-shiny-filter/sample_data.csv` — Sample dataset
